### Stage B: Stage-1-order white-zone postprocess

Main script:

```text
/fs04/scratch2/qb48/chikayoh/xspecies_stage1order_white3_pipeline_20260621/stage1order_white3_postprocess_v2.m
```

Existing array script:

```text
/fs04/scratch2/qb48/chikayoh/xspecies_stage1order_white3_pipeline_20260621/run_stage1order_white3_array.slurm
```

Main inputs:

```text
Stage A t-score MAT
Stage 1 reference MAT
```

Stage 1 reference:

```text
/fs04/scratch2/qb48/chikayoh/stage1_reference_20260621/TS_Normalised_train_macaque_George_ch055_validate_human_376_ch134_accuracy.mat
```

Key visualization parameter:

```text
white_abs_t=3
```

Stage B purpose:

* restrict/reorder features by the Stage 1 feature set/order
* plot AS and SU heatmaps
* show `|t| <= 3` as white as a visualization criterion
* keep visualization white-zone separate from validity masking

### Stage C: Angus clustering/MNI plotting

Angus plotting functions copied to scratch:

```text
/fs04/scratch2/qb48/chikayoh/xspecies_stage1order_white3_pipeline_20260621/angus_plotting_code_20260622/clusterChannels.m
/fs04/scratch2/qb48/chikayoh/xspecies_stage1order_white3_pipeline_20260621/angus_plotting_code_20260622/plotMat_withMNI.m
/fs04/scratch2/qb48/chikayoh/xspecies_stage1order_white3_pipeline_20260621/angus_plotting_code_20260622/MNIcolorbar_example.m
```

Before interpreting MNI colorbars, check:

```text
t-score MAT channel_ids
MNI channelID_all
YY/ZZ vector order
row order after clustering
```

Do not interpret anterior-posterior gradients until channel ID alignment is confirmed.

### Recommended execution order

1. Validate Stage A v4 on 403.
2. Run Stage B on 403 v4 output.
3. Check MNI/channel alignment for 403.
4. Apply Angus clustering/MNI plotting to 403.
5. Expand Stage A to 372/409/423.
6. Expand Stage B and Angus plotting to 372/409/423.
7. Build 2018 subject inventory from `postprocess_HCTSA/human`.
8. Stage and process 2018 subjects.
9. Process 376 only after the source directory question is resolved.

